    "id": "b1_21",
    "title": "21. Have got / Have (Sở hữu)",
    "level": "B1",
    "category": "Verbs",
    "color": "bg-lime-300",
    "theory": [
      {
        "h": "I. HAVE vs HAVE GOT",
        "c": "👉 Cả hai đều nghĩa = CÓ, SỞ HỮU\n→ I have a car. = I have got a car. = I've got a car.\n→ She has a sister. = She has got a sister. = She's got a sister.\n\n📌 HAVE GOT phổ biến hơn ở British English\n📌 HAVE phổ biến hơn ở American English"
      },
      {
        "h": "II. Công thức HAVE GOT",
        "c": "✅ Khẳng định: S + have/has + got + N\n→ I've got a headache. She's got blue eyes.\n❌ Phủ định: S + haven't/hasn't + got + N\n→ I haven't got any money. He hasn't got a car.\n❓ Nghi vấn: Have/Has + S + got + N?\n→ Have you got a pen? Has she got a brother?"
      },
      {
        "h": "III. Khi KHÔNG dùng HAVE GOT",
        "c": "⚠️ HAVE GOT chỉ dùng cho SỞ HỮU ở hiện tại.\nKHÔNG dùng cho:\n- Thói quen: I have breakfast at 7. (KHÔNG: I've got breakfast)\n- Quá khứ: I had a dog. (KHÔNG: I had got a dog)\n- Tương lai: I will have a meeting. (KHÔNG: I will have got)\n- V-ing: I am having lunch. (KHÔNG: I am having got)"
      }
    ],
